- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometric algorithms for computing the smallest enclosing rectangle. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents new algorithms and data structures for solving the problem. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper discusses conditional lower bounds based on the hardness of $(\min,+)$-convolution. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses lower bounds and the complexity of the problem. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the subset sum version of the problem, which is related to game theory and optimization.
